'University of Groningen', 'description': 'Thesis title: "All I chose was blue - A study investigating habitat choice in Lake Victoria cichlids"

Conducted laboratory research investigating habitat choice of two closely related sympatric Lake Victoria cichlid species. These species occur at differing but somewhat overlapping depths in turbid water and thereby are subjected to different light environments. This study aimed to highlight wether there was genetic (species effect) or phenotypic (treatment effect) driver for habitat choice. 

Lab work consisted of testing individuals reared in natural and unnatural lighting environments and videoed trials lasting 6 hours. Conducted both field and laboratory research investigating the presence of a facilitation cascade on mussel beds. More specifically the link between mussel beds and bladder wrack (Fucus vesiculosus). 

Field work consisted of the established and maintenance of plots, regular sampling and counts of Fucus, mussels and oysters and core sampling for in- and epifauna.
